1
00:00:00,070 --> 00:01:02,070
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:01:56,194 --> 00:01:57,330
[Yooseong Villa]

3
00:01:57,330 --> 00:02:00,056
[Episode 2]

4
00:02:08,238 --> 00:02:09,472
Let's go.

5
00:04:11,757 --> 00:04:16,539
[Hyun Jin, I'm sorry.]

6
00:04:26,209 --> 00:04:29,045
Do you really have to turn me
into some kind of burden?

7
00:04:29,045 --> 00:04:30,297
How are you a burden?

8
00:04:30,297 --> 00:04:31,381
I am.

9
00:04:31,381 --> 00:04:33,633
Like this thing stuck to you,
weighing you down.

10
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:34,926
Hyun Jin.

11
00:04:34,926 --> 00:04:37,579
You already have your hands full with Woo Joo,

12
00:04:38,180 --> 00:04:40,623
and you still went out of your way
to make a room for me here.

13
00:04:42,767 --> 00:04:44,127
I'm never moving into this house.

14
00:04:44,978 --> 00:04:46,462
So please...

15
00:04:47,689 --> 00:04:49,340
Just leave me alone.

16
00:05:05,477 --> 00:05:08,324
[BS Food Acceptance Announcement]

17
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:16,244
[BS Food Acceptance Announcement]

18
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:23,374
If only they'd sent it a few days earlier...

19
00:05:25,727 --> 00:05:28,504
Then I wouldn't have fought with my sister...

20
00:05:30,815 --> 00:05:34,385
I wouldn't have said
those awful things to her...

21
00:05:36,863 --> 00:05:38,306
Am I a burden to you?

22
00:05:38,949 --> 00:05:41,076
- Who said that?
- You did.

23
00:05:41,076 --> 00:05:43,161
You haven't even tied the knot

24
00:05:43,161 --> 00:05:44,788
and you've spent your whole life
looking after me.

25
00:05:44,788 --> 00:05:46,522
It's not like I'm nine anymore.

26
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:51,778
Oh, sweetie.

27
00:05:52,587 --> 00:05:54,238
How did you grow up this fast?

28
00:05:55,966 --> 00:05:58,927
Now I'm your mom and dad.

29
00:05:58,927 --> 00:06:01,079
- Really?
- Yeah.

30
00:06:02,097 --> 00:06:04,683
I might not be able to give you the very best,

31
00:06:04,683 --> 00:06:05,934
but I promise to give it my all.

32
00:06:05,934 --> 00:06:08,419
So go ahead and invite
as many guests as you want.

33
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,338
Leave it to me.

34
00:06:19,364 --> 00:06:21,349
I'm sorry.

35
00:06:24,786 --> 00:06:27,622
Mom.

36
00:06:27,622 --> 00:06:30,983
Mom.

37
00:06:32,711 --> 00:06:36,739
Mom.

38
00:06:38,049 --> 00:06:40,451
Mom.

39
00:06:57,027 --> 00:06:59,095
We're closed.

40
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:05,727
Hey, clean this up.

41
00:07:15,462 --> 00:07:16,546
Is something wrong?

42
00:07:16,546 --> 00:07:18,214
Nothing's wrong.

43
00:07:18,214 --> 00:07:20,008
It's just a little celebration.

44
00:07:20,008 --> 00:07:22,719
I'm finally escaping that shoebox of a studio,

45
00:07:22,719 --> 00:07:23,970
moving into a place
where I can do whatever I want with it,

46
00:07:23,970 --> 00:07:25,388
and

47
00:07:25,388 --> 00:07:28,892
where I can actually put holes in the walls.

48
00:07:28,892 --> 00:07:30,293
That's not it, is it?

49
00:07:30,935 --> 00:07:32,103
Whenever something's up

50
00:07:32,103 --> 00:07:33,588
you come here with soju.

51
00:07:36,524 --> 00:07:37,717
Do I?

52
00:07:42,072 --> 00:07:44,724
Remember when you got back
from meeting your brother's in-laws,

53
00:07:45,575 --> 00:07:47,518
you showed up with soju that time too.

54
00:08:05,303 --> 00:08:07,163
This time it's a funeral.

55
00:08:09,599 --> 00:08:10,917
I stood there

56
00:08:12,811 --> 00:08:14,545
as the chief mourner for Sun Woo Jin.

57
00:08:21,986 --> 00:08:23,846
He was apparently such a good person

58
00:08:24,864 --> 00:08:27,951
that everyone was crying talking about him.

59
00:08:27,951 --> 00:08:29,477
But I couldn't shed a single tear.

60
00:08:31,913 --> 00:08:33,731
How could I cry when I barely knew him?

61
00:08:36,418 --> 00:08:39,237
I found out he had a kid
right there at the funeral.

62
00:08:39,963 --> 00:08:41,030
A kid?

63
00:08:41,756 --> 00:08:42,907
Yeah.

64
00:08:43,591 --> 00:08:45,385
They asked me if I was going to raise him.

65
00:08:45,385 --> 00:08:46,553
Are they out of their minds?

66
00:08:46,553 --> 00:08:48,253
Expecting me to just shoulder that burden?

67
00:08:49,431 --> 00:08:50,998
I've never taken care of anything

68
00:08:52,183 --> 00:08:54,310
besides myself,

69
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:56,420
and I'm not about to start now.

70
00:09:01,943 --> 00:09:03,177
You doing alright?

71
00:09:08,741 --> 00:09:10,685
What's there to not be okay about?

72
00:09:12,662 --> 00:09:14,414
I spent more years apart from him

73
00:09:14,414 --> 00:09:16,691
than I ever spent with him.

74
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,159
But

75
00:09:29,179 --> 00:09:31,038
there's one thing that's bugging me.

76
00:09:31,973 --> 00:09:33,291
What's that?

77
00:09:38,188 --> 00:09:39,314
I'll see you next time.

78
00:09:39,314 --> 00:09:41,299
- Yes, take care.
- Thank you.

79
00:09:46,779 --> 00:09:48,281
Tae Hyung, it's me.

80
00:09:48,281 --> 00:09:50,283
There's something I really need to tell you.

81
00:09:50,283 --> 00:09:52,018
I'll be waiting for your call.

82
00:09:53,369 --> 00:09:54,913
The last person

83
00:09:54,913 --> 00:09:57,732
Sun Woo Jin called

84
00:10:00,376 --> 00:10:01,694
was me.

85
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:09,035
Why did he call?

86
00:10:11,429 --> 00:10:13,706
He said he had something important to say,

87
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,501
so what was it?

88
00:10:25,276 --> 00:10:26,636
I gave up wondering

89
00:10:29,572 --> 00:10:31,974
about his life ages ago.

90
00:10:49,968 --> 00:10:52,703
Of course it's raining.

91
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,456
So annoying.

92
00:11:24,544 --> 00:11:25,795
When I

93
00:11:25,795 --> 00:11:28,256
land this job at BS Food,

94
00:11:28,256 --> 00:11:30,491
there's one dish I keep thinking about.

95
00:11:36,059 --> 00:11:39,350
[Work on recipes]
[Ace the interview]

96
00:11:39,350 --> 00:11:40,626
Alright.

97
00:11:45,481 --> 00:11:46,966
I think food offers

98
00:11:47,775 --> 00:11:50,737
so many advantages.

99
00:11:50,737 --> 00:11:51,946
Ta-da.

100
00:11:51,946 --> 00:11:53,556
Come on, try it, Woo Joo.

101
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:57,143
Here, say ah.

102
00:11:58,661 --> 00:12:00,538
Hey, Sun Woo Joo.

103
00:12:00,538 --> 00:12:01,748
I put so much effort into this

104
00:12:01,748 --> 00:12:02,999
practicing for the interview,

105
00:12:02,999 --> 00:12:05,335
so please, one little bite.

106
00:12:05,335 --> 00:12:06,375
Here, ah.

107
00:12:09,339 --> 00:12:11,049
How is it? Good, right?

108
00:12:11,049 --> 00:12:12,300
Right?

109
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:15,094
Here, I'll give you a bigger piece
with some meat.

110
00:12:15,094 --> 00:12:16,512
Alright.

111
00:12:16,512 --> 00:12:18,289
Come on, ah.

112
00:12:20,808 --> 00:12:22,084
Oh, hey.

113
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,838
What a waste.

114
00:12:26,765 --> 00:12:27,774
I don't want it.

115
00:12:27,774 --> 00:12:28,358
No?

116
00:12:28,358 --> 00:12:29,550
Yeah.

117
00:12:32,236 --> 00:12:34,138
- Hyun Jin.
- Se Yeon.

118
00:12:39,452 --> 00:12:40,995
Did you just give up on moving around

119
00:12:40,995 --> 00:12:42,163
and start living in the living room?

120
00:12:42,163 --> 00:12:43,689
Look at this place...

121
00:12:45,208 --> 00:12:46,817
And look at you two...

122
00:12:49,087 --> 00:12:51,197
Parenting is no joke.

123
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:53,675
Tell me what to do. Anything.

124
00:12:53,675 --> 00:12:54,425
Should I tidy up?

125
00:12:54,425 --> 00:12:55,510
Where'd you put your robot vacuum?

126
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:57,095
Got a dishwasher anywhere?

127
00:12:57,095 --> 00:12:57,845
Is the air purifier on?

128
00:12:57,845 --> 00:12:59,305
What can I help with?

129
00:12:59,305 --> 00:13:00,831
I'm great at pressing buttons.

130
00:13:03,101 --> 00:13:04,710
Okay, then...

131
00:13:05,478 --> 00:13:06,754
Could you...

132
00:13:12,777 --> 00:13:15,113
How's that? Feeling a bit cooler now?

133
00:13:15,113 --> 00:13:17,115
Oh, so much better.

134
00:13:17,115 --> 00:13:18,724
I can actually live again.

135
00:13:19,784 --> 00:13:20,910
That's a relief.

136
00:13:20,910 --> 00:13:23,016
Finished.

137
00:13:23,016 --> 00:13:24,038
Oh, right.

138
00:13:24,038 --> 00:13:26,582
How's the interview prep going for my company?

139
00:13:26,582 --> 00:13:27,375
Yes.

140
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:30,294
I'm going to crush the BS Food interview.

141
00:13:30,294 --> 00:13:31,504
I have to get in

142
00:13:31,504 --> 00:13:33,923
so I can raise Woo Joo right.

143
00:13:33,923 --> 00:13:35,133
Love that energy.

144
00:13:35,133 --> 00:13:37,427
Let me dig around at work

145
00:13:37,427 --> 00:13:40,012
and get you all the inside info on that team.

146
00:13:40,012 --> 00:13:41,747
Thanks so much.

147
00:13:42,932 --> 00:13:45,143
Oh, but here's the thing.

148
00:13:45,143 --> 00:13:46,144
What?

149
00:13:46,144 --> 00:13:47,812
Who's going to watch Woo Joo

150
00:13:47,812 --> 00:13:49,361
on interview day?

151
00:13:49,361 --> 00:13:51,588
What's the problem?
I can take care of Woo Joo that day.

152
00:13:51,588 --> 00:13:53,359
Wait, don't you have work?

153
00:13:53,359 --> 00:13:54,652
I'll kill thirty in the break room,

154
00:13:54,652 --> 00:13:55,945
another thirty at the cafe,

155
00:13:55,945 --> 00:13:57,405
then slip out

156
00:13:57,405 --> 00:13:59,615
saying I need to hit the bank. I got you.

157
00:13:59,615 --> 00:14:00,908
You're the best.

158
00:14:00,908 --> 00:14:02,434
Okay, Woo Joo.

159
00:14:03,619 --> 00:14:04,854
Hey.

160
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:06,814
You okay?

161
00:14:08,082 --> 00:14:09,400
Woo Joo.

162
00:14:10,376 --> 00:14:11,861
Let's get you cleaned up...

163
00:14:13,004 --> 00:14:14,005
Wait, hold on...

164
00:14:14,005 --> 00:14:15,131
Woo Joo, this is where you go potty...

165
00:14:15,131 --> 00:14:16,518
- No, no.
- Don't do it there...

166
00:14:18,342 --> 00:14:19,719
Wrong spot.

167
00:14:19,719 --> 00:14:21,180
- No.
- Hold on tight.

168
00:14:31,147 --> 00:14:33,465
- This is insane.
- This is insane.

169
00:14:34,942 --> 00:14:37,236
They're only adorable every now and then.

170
00:14:37,236 --> 00:14:39,572
Way more precious

171
00:14:39,572 --> 00:14:41,265
from a distance.

172
00:14:41,991 --> 00:14:43,559
Same goes for Woo Joo.

173
00:14:45,453 --> 00:14:46,739
Hey.

174
00:14:47,371 --> 00:14:49,624
Seriously, how are you planning
to do this by yourself?

175
00:14:49,624 --> 00:14:51,042
Will you actually be fine?

176
00:14:51,042 --> 00:14:53,961
I was only here for a bit
and I'm already drained.

177
00:14:53,961 --> 00:14:55,463
I'll manage.

178
00:14:55,463 --> 00:14:57,006
Things should get better

179
00:14:57,006 --> 00:14:59,884
once my arm's healed up.

180
00:14:59,884 --> 00:15:00,968
So

181
00:15:00,968 --> 00:15:02,970
that Pimang jerk who did this to your arm

182
00:15:02,970 --> 00:15:04,330
hasn't even called?

183
00:15:07,183 --> 00:15:08,601
No conscience,

184
00:15:08,601 --> 00:15:09,811
no sense of responsibility.

185
00:15:09,811 --> 00:15:11,270
Whatever, screw him.

186
00:15:11,270 --> 00:15:12,605
Woo Joo and I will get by

187
00:15:12,605 --> 00:15:14,190
perfectly fine without him.

188
00:15:14,190 --> 00:15:16,926
He's probably off
living his best life somewhere.

189
00:15:22,052 --> 00:15:23,825
So this is the look I want for the kitchen,

190
00:15:23,825 --> 00:15:26,035
and this is for the living room.

191
00:15:26,035 --> 00:15:28,371
And over here,

192
00:15:28,371 --> 00:15:30,915
I need the outlets
completely flush with the wall.

193
00:15:30,915 --> 00:15:34,126
This is where the TV and soundbar will go,

194
00:15:34,126 --> 00:15:34,836
so I need a quad outlet.

195
00:15:34,836 --> 00:15:38,214
That's really not an easy job.

196
00:15:38,214 --> 00:15:41,509
Once the TV goes up, you won't even see it.

197
00:15:41,509 --> 00:15:43,636
I can't wrap my head around

198
00:15:43,636 --> 00:15:44,720
doing recessed work

199
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,180
in a place this old...

200
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:48,516
They said it's possible
if you open up the floor.

201
00:15:48,516 --> 00:15:49,934
I absolutely need

202
00:15:49,934 --> 00:15:52,019
everything to look clean inside.

203
00:15:52,019 --> 00:15:53,771
Well if you're such an expert,

204
00:15:53,771 --> 00:15:55,523
do it yourself then.

205
00:15:55,523 --> 00:15:58,442
If I tear up the floor like you're suggesting

206
00:15:58,442 --> 00:16:00,027
and accidentally hit the plumbing,

207
00:16:00,027 --> 00:16:01,612
we're looking at a flood.

208
00:16:01,612 --> 00:16:03,823
And if this unit and the one downstairs both
get water damage,

209
00:16:03,823 --> 00:16:05,074
are you going to cover that?

210
00:16:05,074 --> 00:16:06,492
That's exactly

211
00:16:06,492 --> 00:16:08,452
why I'm spending money

212
00:16:08,452 --> 00:16:11,438
to hire someone with your expertise.

213
00:16:12,832 --> 00:16:15,376
I'm already giving you a deal,

214
00:16:15,376 --> 00:16:16,752
a huge deal,

215
00:16:16,752 --> 00:16:17,879
actually the biggest deal possible,

216
00:16:17,879 --> 00:16:21,591
but you keep piling on requests

217
00:16:21,591 --> 00:16:23,467
and I can't make any progress.

218
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:25,761
I'm begging you here.

219
00:16:25,761 --> 00:16:28,055
We need this done right
so we can start on the floors

220
00:16:28,055 --> 00:16:29,599
and tiles,

221
00:16:29,599 --> 00:16:32,339
and actually move in on time.

222
00:16:42,382 --> 00:16:43,926
Oh my, look at the veins on his hands.

223
00:16:49,368 --> 00:16:50,602
Gosh.

224
00:16:57,043 --> 00:16:58,819
His knife skills are amazing.

225
00:17:23,298 --> 00:17:24,403
What do we have here!

226
00:17:24,403 --> 00:17:26,656
The bok choy salad has a bolder seasoning,

227
00:17:26,656 --> 00:17:28,366
tailored for single folks.

228
00:17:28,366 --> 00:17:29,909
For the wild chive greens
doenjang tofu pancake,

229
00:17:29,909 --> 00:17:32,119
I let the fragrance do the heavy lifting.

230
00:17:32,119 --> 00:17:33,663
And this one's

231
00:17:33,663 --> 00:17:35,147
purely for show.

232
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:39,943
Let me try some.

233
00:17:43,798 --> 00:17:45,202
Of course.

234
00:17:46,008 --> 00:17:48,135
The cafeteria is empty because everyone's off

235
00:17:48,135 --> 00:17:49,679
to taste your cooking here.

236
00:17:49,679 --> 00:17:50,930
This crowd is double

237
00:17:50,930 --> 00:17:53,057
what we had at the "Today's Meal" launch.

238
00:17:53,057 --> 00:17:57,144
Team 3 has topped sales
three consecutive times now.

239
00:17:57,144 --> 00:17:59,939
We couldn't have done it
without the directors backing us.

240
00:17:59,939 --> 00:18:02,942
Order volume has already
tripled our original goal,

241
00:18:02,942 --> 00:18:06,595
so we're still on
for that production line expansion, correct?

242
00:18:07,446 --> 00:18:09,031
And Director Kim,

243
00:18:09,031 --> 00:18:11,659
you're aware we've got
another project in development, right?

244
00:18:11,659 --> 00:18:14,245
How many projects are you running at once?

245
00:18:14,245 --> 00:18:14,954
Doesn't that wear you out?

246
00:18:14,954 --> 00:18:17,707
If you all greenlight things quickly,
it's really no problem.

247
00:18:17,707 --> 00:18:19,542
I'll have the proposal to you

248
00:18:19,542 --> 00:18:21,544
by three this afternoon then.

249
00:18:21,544 --> 00:18:23,590
There you go again.

250
00:18:23,590 --> 00:18:27,076
With you delivering winners back to back,

251
00:18:27,076 --> 00:18:29,969
how come you keep having vacancies?

252
00:18:29,969 --> 00:18:31,637
That's why we're hiring someone new soon.

253
00:18:31,637 --> 00:18:33,080
Yeah.

254
00:18:38,936 --> 00:18:40,479
Mr. Park.

255
00:18:40,479 --> 00:18:42,440
Was the whole vein display

256
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,216
really necessary though?

257
00:18:45,317 --> 00:18:48,137
I mean, I was impressed too.

258
00:18:49,879 --> 00:18:53,506
How'd you lock down
the production line expansion on the spot,

259
00:18:53,506 --> 00:18:56,770
plus get the green light
for the new product so effortlessly...

260
00:18:59,248 --> 00:19:02,365
Was all that showmanship intentional?

261
00:19:02,365 --> 00:19:03,911
You plan with your head,

262
00:19:03,911 --> 00:19:06,155
but you persuade with your body.

263
00:19:07,047 --> 00:19:08,049
Excuse me?

264
00:19:08,049 --> 00:19:10,426
One cooking demo beats a hundred meetings.

265
00:19:10,426 --> 00:19:11,969
They never

266
00:19:11,969 --> 00:19:13,662
look at the actual documents anyway.

267
00:19:15,306 --> 00:19:16,766
Classic you!

268
00:19:16,766 --> 00:19:19,042
- Nice work.
- Great work.

269
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:25,274
Since you'll be swamped with work again,

270
00:19:25,274 --> 00:19:27,526
I'll take care of meeting the new candidates.

271
00:19:27,526 --> 00:19:29,128
Here's the list of candidates.

272
00:19:29,128 --> 00:19:30,404
[Park Yoon Seong]
Thanks.

273
00:19:40,334 --> 00:19:42,417
[Woo Hyun Jin]

274
00:19:51,675 --> 00:19:53,024
Yoon Seong.

275
00:20:25,635 --> 00:20:27,700
[What matters more than taste is the concept!]

276
00:20:37,201 --> 00:20:39,225
Oh, my baby.

277
00:20:39,225 --> 00:20:41,093
Finally in my hands.

278
00:20:41,093 --> 00:20:42,561
[Purchase Now]

279
00:20:43,915 --> 00:20:44,923
[Purchase Complete]

280
00:20:53,153 --> 00:20:54,812
[D-Day Interview]

281
00:20:55,948 --> 00:20:59,285
The police car comes with its sirens on.

282
00:20:59,285 --> 00:21:02,104
The construction needs to be done by that time.

283
00:21:02,776 --> 00:21:04,427
Alright, thanks.

284
00:21:40,117 --> 00:21:41,348
Woo Joo.

285
00:21:41,348 --> 00:21:42,661
Yeah.

286
00:21:42,661 --> 00:21:45,164
I'm definitely getting this job today,

287
00:21:45,164 --> 00:21:47,774
and I'm going to whip up
an omakase-style feast for you.

288
00:21:51,795 --> 00:21:53,839
Yeah, once I give Woo Joo breakfast,
I'll leave...

289
00:21:53,839 --> 00:21:56,070
I'm being dragged to Busan right now.

290
00:21:56,070 --> 00:21:57,092
What?

291
00:21:57,092 --> 00:21:58,886
Seriously, I think my boss has gone crazy.

292
00:21:58,886 --> 00:22:01,222
I was forced to go to this food truck thing.

293
00:22:01,222 --> 00:22:02,681
What do I do?

294
00:22:02,681 --> 00:22:03,724
Should I just quit?

295
00:22:03,724 --> 00:22:05,178
Or should I ask my mom for help?

296
00:22:05,178 --> 00:22:06,435
No.

297
00:22:06,435 --> 00:22:08,729
I can figure this out on my own.

298
00:22:08,729 --> 00:22:10,689
Stop stressing and just focus on your trip.

299
00:22:10,689 --> 00:22:11,941
I'm so sorry.

300
00:22:11,941 --> 00:22:13,342
Sorry.

301
00:22:17,967 --> 00:22:19,025
[Two hours before the interview]

302
00:22:19,025 --> 00:22:21,200
[Next door]

303
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,961
[Not home]
Excuse me, I live right next door.

304
00:22:23,961 --> 00:22:25,496
[Downstairs]

305
00:22:25,496 --> 00:22:26,855
Just a moment.

306
00:22:29,575 --> 00:22:32,294
Hello, I'm Woo Joo's auntie.

307
00:22:32,294 --> 00:22:33,587
I know who you are.

308
00:22:33,587 --> 00:22:35,631
I've bumped into you a couple of times before.

309
00:22:35,631 --> 00:22:37,424
I hate to bother you like this,

310
00:22:37,424 --> 00:22:39,760
but I've got a job interview today,

311
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:41,718
and I was wondering if you could look after him

312
00:22:41,718 --> 00:22:43,910
for a couple of hours?

313
00:22:43,910 --> 00:22:45,140
Oh, what should I do...

314
00:22:45,140 --> 00:22:46,958
We're heading to my in-laws' right now.

315
00:22:51,744 --> 00:22:53,816
[Phone contacts]

316
00:22:53,816 --> 00:22:55,526
- Hey, Ye Eun.
- What, me?

317
00:22:55,526 --> 00:22:57,611
Even if I'm off today,
I can't just watch a kid.

318
00:22:57,611 --> 00:22:59,012
I'm sorry.

319
00:22:59,697 --> 00:23:00,656
Hey, Hyun Young.

320
00:23:00,656 --> 00:23:01,865
I'm sorry.

321
00:23:01,865 --> 00:23:03,884
My boyfriend and I are checking out
wedding venues today.

322
00:23:03,884 --> 00:23:05,243
[One hour before the interview]

323
00:23:13,217 --> 00:23:15,150
What do I do now...

324
00:23:15,957 --> 00:23:17,759
I'm completely stuck...

325
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:23,227
Great work today.

326
00:23:23,227 --> 00:23:24,311
Let's get something refreshing.

327
00:23:24,311 --> 00:23:26,213
Yeah, you all worked hard.

328
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:29,675
Is it a renovation or something?

329
00:23:31,304 --> 00:23:33,027
I have a huge problem.

330
00:23:33,027 --> 00:23:35,740
There's something I need
to discuss with you right away.

331
00:23:37,694 --> 00:23:39,207
I'm...

332
00:23:40,758 --> 00:23:42,663
about to give up on Woo Joo.

333
00:23:42,663 --> 00:23:44,415
What?

334
00:23:44,415 --> 00:23:46,024
She's giving up the kid?

335
00:23:59,753 --> 00:24:02,436
Just three hours, I swear.

336
00:24:03,188 --> 00:24:04,732
So what you're saying is

337
00:24:04,732 --> 00:24:06,525
you want me to watch the kid

338
00:24:06,525 --> 00:24:07,776
while you're at your interview?

339
00:24:07,776 --> 00:24:08,736
That's right.

340
00:24:08,736 --> 00:24:09,862
I tried everything I could

341
00:24:09,862 --> 00:24:12,197
to handle this myself,

342
00:24:12,197 --> 00:24:14,033
but nobody compares to you.

343
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:15,993
You're super responsible,

344
00:24:15,993 --> 00:24:17,953
and you and Woo Joo have amazing chemistry.

345
00:24:17,953 --> 00:24:19,896
More like a disaster, actually.

346
00:24:23,585 --> 00:24:25,539
Hey, get off.

347
00:24:25,539 --> 00:24:27,051
- I said get off.
- See?

348
00:24:27,051 --> 00:24:29,798
Woo Joo is so attached to you.

349
00:24:29,798 --> 00:24:32,468
To be honest, if you don't mind,

350
00:24:32,468 --> 00:24:34,511
I'd love to raise Woo Joo here
with you anytime.

351
00:24:34,511 --> 00:24:35,596
Have you lost your mind?

352
00:24:35,596 --> 00:24:36,680
I already said I won't take care of him.

353
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,015
And I'm not even his uncle.

354
00:24:38,015 --> 00:24:39,350
Listen.

355
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:42,311
It's been over three years since we met,

356
00:24:42,311 --> 00:24:44,757
and when a man and a woman spend
two nights together,

357
00:24:44,757 --> 00:24:45,940
words aren't necessary between them.

358
00:24:45,940 --> 00:24:46,899
Seriously, what are you saying?

359
00:24:46,899 --> 00:24:48,692
None of that would've happened
if your arm was fine.

360
00:24:48,692 --> 00:24:50,027
That's my point.

361
00:24:50,027 --> 00:24:52,679
You owe me for this arm.

362
00:24:56,325 --> 00:24:57,701
My poor baby Woo Joo.

363
00:24:57,701 --> 00:24:58,494
Oh, come on.

364
00:24:58,494 --> 00:25:00,204
I can barely look after him

365
00:25:00,204 --> 00:25:02,873
with my arm like this,

366
00:25:02,873 --> 00:25:04,750
and all the other applicants

367
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:06,919
are going to walk in with both arms working.

368
00:25:06,919 --> 00:25:09,505
And BS apparently has amazing perks.

369
00:25:09,505 --> 00:25:11,590
If I miss this interview,

370
00:25:11,590 --> 00:25:14,326
what'll become of Woo Joo?

371
00:25:27,898 --> 00:25:29,274
Raise him yourself,

372
00:25:29,274 --> 00:25:30,842
and I'm cutting ties.

373
00:25:33,070 --> 00:25:34,446
You can't just cut ties whenever you want.

374
00:25:34,446 --> 00:25:35,781
We're connected by blood.

375
00:25:35,781 --> 00:25:37,741
Sorry, but we don't share
a single drop of blood.

376
00:25:37,741 --> 00:25:40,244
But Woo Joo does.

377
00:25:40,244 --> 00:25:41,704
Plus

378
00:25:41,704 --> 00:25:43,211
we've already

379
00:25:49,712 --> 00:25:51,780
stripped together.

380
00:25:54,633 --> 00:25:57,119
Stripped? When did that happen?

381
00:25:58,929 --> 00:26:00,438
The bubble wrap.

382
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:06,812
Be careful.

383
00:26:06,812 --> 00:26:08,772
Don't let my baby get scratched.

384
00:26:08,772 --> 00:26:10,399
Easy!

385
00:26:10,399 --> 00:26:12,134
There we go.

386
00:26:14,792 --> 00:26:16,171
The bubble wrap.

387
00:26:17,156 --> 00:26:18,907
Come on...

388
00:26:18,907 --> 00:26:20,492
This place belongs to Woo Joo,

389
00:26:20,492 --> 00:26:21,744
so treat it like it's yours

390
00:26:21,744 --> 00:26:23,175
and relax.

391
00:26:23,175 --> 00:26:24,516
Woo Joo, bye.

392
00:26:30,495 --> 00:26:31,591
Wait!

393
00:26:31,591 --> 00:26:33,989
Don't you dare give him chocolate.

394
00:26:52,568 --> 00:26:55,261
[Self-Introduction Letter Secrets]

395
00:27:34,358 --> 00:27:36,593
These photos turned out like crap.

396
00:27:43,075 --> 00:27:43,784
Yes, hello?

397
00:27:43,784 --> 00:27:44,618
Danny.

398
00:27:44,618 --> 00:27:46,120
Could you email me that document from before?

399
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:47,955
It's urgent, so please do it right now.

400
00:27:47,955 --> 00:27:50,315
Oh, right now...

401
00:27:51,013 --> 00:27:52,583
Yes, got it.

402
00:28:15,065 --> 00:28:17,359
We should develop an approach
based on consumer habits

403
00:28:17,359 --> 00:28:19,069
across different age groups.

404
00:28:19,069 --> 00:28:21,905
People living alone tend to go
for cheap and easy meals,

405
00:28:21,905 --> 00:28:25,047
which means they shop at convenience stores
and buy small portions online.

406
00:28:25,047 --> 00:28:27,286
[Interview Waiting Room]

407
00:28:27,286 --> 00:28:30,581
Park Ji Won, Cha Young Seok, Joo Hyun Sun,

408
00:28:30,581 --> 00:28:31,940
please come in.

409
00:28:35,905 --> 00:28:38,178
[Interview Admission Ticket]

410
00:28:45,012 --> 00:28:46,955
I wonder if Woo Joo's doing okay.

411
00:29:02,751 --> 00:29:03,780
Hey, kid.

412
00:29:03,780 --> 00:29:06,867
You only have to remember three things.

413
00:29:06,867 --> 00:29:08,243
Don't move.

414
00:29:08,243 --> 00:29:10,078
Keep calm and don't move.

415
00:29:10,078 --> 00:29:11,330
Act invisible,

416
00:29:11,330 --> 00:29:13,665
silent as a ghost, and don't move.

417
00:29:13,665 --> 00:29:15,459
Okay.

418
00:29:15,459 --> 00:29:18,194
Wait, did you actually get that?

419
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,328
Let's see.

420
00:29:34,353 --> 00:29:36,421
Oh, come on...

421
00:29:39,066 --> 00:29:41,610
Is it okay for a 20-month-old
to have a hamburger?

422
00:29:41,610 --> 00:29:42,611
For a 20-month-old,

423
00:29:42,611 --> 00:29:44,780
meat patties and bread are a little premature,

424
00:29:44,780 --> 00:29:47,307
but a few French fries should be fine.

425
00:29:48,116 --> 00:29:50,702
Well, it says too early,
not that it's forbidden.

426
00:29:50,702 --> 00:29:52,079
Okay.

427
00:29:52,079 --> 00:29:55,207
Time to introduce you
to the finer things early.

428
00:29:55,207 --> 00:29:56,733
Here.

429
00:30:00,045 --> 00:30:02,322
Give it to me!

430
00:30:06,510 --> 00:30:07,719
How is it?

431
00:30:07,719 --> 00:30:09,721
Best thing you've ever tasted, huh?

432
00:30:09,721 --> 00:30:11,331
Yeah.

433
00:30:16,019 --> 00:30:17,671
Here, say ah.

434
00:30:22,818 --> 00:30:24,177
Good, right?

435
00:30:26,113 --> 00:30:28,657
Another life-changing moment for you, huh?

436
00:30:28,657 --> 00:30:29,849
Dad.

437
00:30:35,455 --> 00:30:36,856
Go on, have some more.

438
00:31:11,408 --> 00:31:13,994
This is no joke.

439
00:31:13,994 --> 00:31:15,395
For me, food serves

440
00:31:16,038 --> 00:31:19,291
as a key that unlocks my memories.

441
00:31:19,291 --> 00:31:20,332
Back when I was

442
00:31:20,332 --> 00:31:21,098
[2025 First-Half BS Food
Open Recruitment Interview]

443
00:31:21,098 --> 00:31:24,211
rejected at the BS Food final interview
three years ago,

444
00:31:26,173 --> 00:31:28,133
I had a kimchi pancake

445
00:31:28,133 --> 00:31:29,868
that my sister cooked for me.

446
00:31:31,386 --> 00:31:32,763
That dish holds

447
00:31:32,763 --> 00:31:34,890
a special place in my heart.

448
00:31:34,890 --> 00:31:36,016
Whenever it rained,

449
00:31:36,016 --> 00:31:38,018
to cheer me up,

450
00:31:38,018 --> 00:31:40,687
my sister would throw in cheese one day

451
00:31:40,687 --> 00:31:43,256
and corn the next.

452
00:31:44,649 --> 00:31:46,276
All of those moments

453
00:31:46,276 --> 00:31:49,029
are tucked away somewhere dear to me.

454
00:31:49,029 --> 00:31:50,430
To me, that represents

455
00:31:51,114 --> 00:31:53,850
what happens when food carries meaning.

456
00:31:55,243 --> 00:31:58,121
Should I become part of BS Food,

457
00:31:58,121 --> 00:31:59,581
I hope to create products

458
00:31:59,581 --> 00:32:02,250
that effortlessly evoke

459
00:32:02,250 --> 00:32:05,403
cherished memories for consumers.

460
00:33:10,110 --> 00:33:11,570
What's that noise?

461
00:33:11,570 --> 00:33:13,054
Why is there so much noise?

462
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:17,159
You have no reason to be crying.

463
00:33:17,159 --> 00:33:19,269
I should be the one in tears!

464
00:33:34,176 --> 00:33:35,451
No.

465
00:33:40,557 --> 00:33:41,875
No.

466
00:33:47,939 --> 00:33:49,274
Seriously...

467
00:33:49,274 --> 00:33:50,609
Mama.

468
00:33:50,609 --> 00:33:51,926
Because of you...

469
00:33:53,862 --> 00:33:56,222
You're quiet again now that we're outside.

470
00:33:57,115 --> 00:33:58,308
I want that.

471
00:33:59,284 --> 00:34:01,144
- Why are you so heavy?
- Dad.

472
00:34:03,121 --> 00:34:04,501
I want that.

473
00:34:04,501 --> 00:34:05,624
[In-law]

474
00:34:05,624 --> 00:34:06,941
I want that.

475
00:34:38,740 --> 00:34:40,141
Sweetie, you shouldn't do that.

476
00:34:42,077 --> 00:34:44,329
Sweetie, where'd Mommy go?

477
00:34:44,329 --> 00:34:45,605
No.

478
00:35:10,397 --> 00:35:11,644
What?

479
00:35:17,112 --> 00:35:19,101
Honey, over here, here!

480
00:35:22,993 --> 00:35:24,869
I can't be the only one going down.

481
00:35:24,869 --> 00:35:26,502
Now it's your turn to suffer.

482
00:35:27,330 --> 00:35:30,000
Honey, how was your interview?

483
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:31,304
What the hell.

484
00:35:34,768 --> 00:35:35,797
Come on.

485
00:35:35,797 --> 00:35:36,923
Honey?

486
00:35:36,923 --> 00:35:39,843
Are you insane? Why would you come here?

487
00:35:39,843 --> 00:35:42,203
You're unbelievable, you liar.

488
00:35:44,055 --> 00:35:45,765
Well,

489
00:35:45,765 --> 00:35:48,810
I couldn't walk into an interview
wearing a cast.

490
00:35:48,810 --> 00:35:50,228
I just removed it

491
00:35:50,228 --> 00:35:51,563
for a little bit.

492
00:35:51,563 --> 00:35:52,731
That's just how things work.

493
00:35:52,731 --> 00:35:53,982
Whatever.

494
00:35:53,982 --> 00:35:55,383
Take him back.

495
00:36:01,906 --> 00:36:03,299
Are you crazy?

496
00:36:04,409 --> 00:36:05,869
You're calling me crazy

497
00:36:05,869 --> 00:36:06,953
instead of saying thank you?

498
00:36:06,953 --> 00:36:09,205
No, I'm asking if you're out of your mind.

499
00:36:09,205 --> 00:36:10,665
How did you watch him?

500
00:36:10,665 --> 00:36:11,875
And look at the mess you made at the company...

501
00:36:11,875 --> 00:36:13,043
I'm a victim here too.

502
00:36:13,043 --> 00:36:14,169
My personal sanctuary is now

503
00:36:14,169 --> 00:36:16,320
destroyed property and mental trauma.

504
00:36:24,596 --> 00:36:25,847
Take him, now.

505
00:36:25,847 --> 00:36:27,724
Wait, I need to grab some diapers first.

506
00:36:27,724 --> 00:36:29,643
Just take him.

507
00:36:29,643 --> 00:36:32,437
I said wait a minute!

508
00:36:32,437 --> 00:36:34,397
You can handle the diaper situation yourself.

509
00:36:34,397 --> 00:36:36,191
I'm leaving.

510
00:36:36,191 --> 00:36:37,776
Wait, where are you going?

511
00:36:37,776 --> 00:36:39,527
You're supposed to help fix this, Uncle.

512
00:36:39,527 --> 00:36:41,529
How many times do I have to say
I'm not his uncle!

513
00:36:41,529 --> 00:36:42,764
He's...

514
00:36:47,494 --> 00:36:48,662
Woo Joo...

515
00:36:48,662 --> 00:36:51,039
He disappeared.

516
00:36:51,039 --> 00:36:52,690
- Woo Joo.
- Sweetie.

517
00:37:00,382 --> 00:37:01,783
Woo Joo!

518
00:37:05,720 --> 00:37:07,497
- Sweetie, come here!
- Woo Joo!

519
00:37:10,809 --> 00:37:12,018
You go in there, hurry.

520
00:37:12,018 --> 00:37:13,645
How am I supposed to go in?

521
00:37:13,645 --> 00:37:16,036
You're the kid's aunt, hurry up and go in.

522
00:37:16,036 --> 00:37:17,107
Sweetie!

523
00:37:17,107 --> 00:37:18,693
Come here, sweetie, come here.

524
00:37:38,767 --> 00:37:40,088
- Woo Joo!
- Where'd the baby go?

525
00:37:40,088 --> 00:37:41,464
Where?

526
00:37:41,464 --> 00:37:42,298
Over there.

527
00:37:42,298 --> 00:37:43,299
Woo Joo.

528
00:37:43,299 --> 00:37:44,527
Woo Joo.

529
00:37:45,635 --> 00:37:46,761
Woo Joo.

530
00:37:46,761 --> 00:37:48,287
Woo Joo.

531
00:37:50,932 --> 00:37:52,250
Woo Joo.

532
00:38:09,868 --> 00:38:11,102
Woo Joo.

533
00:38:14,664 --> 00:38:17,333
Seriously, let's never cross paths again.

534
00:38:17,333 --> 00:38:18,418
Same goes for you, Woo Joo.

535
00:38:18,418 --> 00:38:20,027
Look who's talking.

536
00:38:29,179 --> 00:38:30,263
Woo Joo.

537
00:38:30,263 --> 00:38:32,307
Your uncle...

538
00:38:32,307 --> 00:38:34,017
I mean, Sun Tae Hyung.

539
00:38:34,017 --> 00:38:36,043
What is wrong with him?

540
00:38:37,562 --> 00:38:38,938
Did something happen today?

541
00:38:38,938 --> 00:38:41,441
What did you do? What did you eat?

542
00:38:41,441 --> 00:38:44,110
Oh, never mind.

543
00:38:44,110 --> 00:38:46,095
Let's not think about him.

544
00:38:50,533 --> 00:38:53,090
Thanks, you caught a fish.

545
00:39:19,143 --> 00:39:22,171
With the baby out of my life, it's so peaceful.

546
00:39:25,485 --> 00:39:26,928
Perfect.

547
00:39:51,399 --> 00:39:53,012
Why aren't you answering your phone?

548
00:39:53,012 --> 00:39:55,665
Your place is flooded right now.

549
00:39:56,388 --> 00:39:58,240
I warned you about that foundation, didn't I?

550
00:39:58,240 --> 00:40:00,934
The plumbing completely exploded.

551
00:40:05,525 --> 00:40:07,110
If I'd been able to reach you yesterday,

552
00:40:07,110 --> 00:40:09,654
none of this would've happened.

553
00:40:09,654 --> 00:40:11,948
We lost our only chance to fix it.

554
00:40:11,948 --> 00:40:13,825
Something unexpected came up yesterday

555
00:40:13,825 --> 00:40:14,868
and my phone got wrecked...

556
00:40:14,868 --> 00:40:19,539
I warned you this job was dangerous.

557
00:40:19,539 --> 00:40:21,541
So what's going to happen to my place?

558
00:40:21,541 --> 00:40:23,585
What do you mean what happens?
The work's delayed.

559
00:40:23,585 --> 00:40:25,169
We need to wait for it to dry

560
00:40:25,169 --> 00:40:27,571
before anyone can start again.

561
00:40:28,464 --> 00:40:29,740
Sir.

562
00:40:30,550 --> 00:40:31,930
So when will I

563
00:40:32,719 --> 00:40:34,954
be able to move in?

564
00:40:36,222 --> 00:40:38,446
At least another month.

565
00:40:38,446 --> 00:40:39,517
We need to wrap up

566
00:40:39,517 --> 00:40:41,669
before the next team can come in.

567
00:40:43,771 --> 00:40:45,398
Sir...

568
00:40:45,398 --> 00:40:46,841
Oh, this...

569
00:40:49,805 --> 00:40:51,430
The electrical work isn't done,
so I'll come back later.

570
00:40:51,430 --> 00:40:53,047
The walls need to be dry
before we can start the wallpaper work.

571
00:40:53,047 --> 00:40:54,847
This is the management office.
There's a leak reported downstairs.

572
00:40:54,847 --> 00:40:55,380
Please contact me.

573
00:40:55,380 --> 00:40:56,214
[Electrical work, ten days]

574
00:40:56,214 --> 00:40:57,090
[Wallpaper, ten days]

575
00:40:57,090 --> 00:40:58,786
[Tile, ten days]

576
00:40:58,786 --> 00:41:00,093
No.

577
00:41:00,093 --> 00:41:03,221
[So where am I supposed to live...]

578
00:41:03,221 --> 00:41:06,252
Stop. Please stop.

579
00:41:06,252 --> 00:41:07,570
Come on, stop.

580
00:41:08,254 --> 00:41:09,881
Stop!

581
00:41:09,881 --> 00:41:11,215
Oh, no...

582
00:41:11,215 --> 00:41:12,342
Thank you.

583
00:41:12,342 --> 00:41:14,327
Just leave it there.

584
00:41:15,066 --> 00:41:17,903
[Your delivery has been completed]

585
00:41:19,905 --> 00:41:20,975
No.

586
00:41:20,975 --> 00:41:23,144
With this heat and moisture...

587
00:41:23,144 --> 00:41:24,670
my babies are going to suffer.

588
00:41:25,705 --> 00:41:26,773
If that little brat

589
00:41:26,773 --> 00:41:28,483
hadn't wrecked my phone...

590
00:41:28,483 --> 00:41:30,860
No, if that woman

591
00:41:30,860 --> 00:41:31,945
had never dumped the kid on me...

592
00:41:31,945 --> 00:41:32,987
No!

593
00:41:32,987 --> 00:41:34,989
If only we hadn't crossed paths
at the funeral...

594
00:41:34,989 --> 00:41:36,032
Actually, going back
to the first family meeting...

595
00:41:36,032 --> 00:41:36,950
No, all the way back to Pimang...

596
00:41:36,950 --> 00:41:38,184
No!

597
00:41:40,008 --> 00:41:42,327
I swear on my life

598
00:41:44,290 --> 00:41:46,275
I will never deal with her again.

599
00:41:50,463 --> 00:41:51,547
My precious babies.

600
00:41:51,547 --> 00:41:52,887
I'm going to keep my babies safe.

601
00:41:52,887 --> 00:41:55,051
Any chance I could stay
one more month in the studio...

602
00:41:55,051 --> 00:41:57,387
The next tenant already signed.

603
00:41:57,387 --> 00:41:59,305
[Storage service]
My piece measures 800 millimeters across.

604
00:41:59,305 --> 00:42:00,932
You'd have to book immediately,

605
00:42:00,932 --> 00:42:01,724
but the wait list is pretty long.

606
00:42:01,724 --> 00:42:03,685
This is a tiny studio apartment.
I can't fit furniture like a sofa in here.

607
00:42:03,685 --> 00:42:05,566
Didn't you always say
your home would never betray you?

608
00:42:05,566 --> 00:42:07,009
Guess it betrayed you?

609
00:42:16,883 --> 00:42:24,883
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

610
00:42:18,908 --> 00:42:20,743
All right.

611
00:42:20,743 --> 00:42:22,704
Keep coming.

612
00:42:22,704 --> 00:42:24,230
Keep coming.

613
00:42:25,415 --> 00:42:26,749
This way, this way.

614
00:42:26,749 --> 00:42:28,084
Keep coming.

615
00:42:28,084 --> 00:42:29,527
Keep coming.

616
00:42:30,461 --> 00:42:33,464
Okay, this way, this way.

617
00:42:33,464 --> 00:42:34,674
Not that way,

618
00:42:34,674 --> 00:42:36,467
this way!

619
00:42:36,467 --> 00:42:37,719
Oh my, hey...

620
00:42:37,719 --> 00:42:39,721
Oh my, the peppers, the peppers!

621
00:42:39,721 --> 00:42:41,139
Stop, stop.

622
00:42:41,139 --> 00:42:42,849
Whoa, seriously,

623
00:42:42,849 --> 00:42:45,000
you're driving all over the peppers!

624
00:42:49,272 --> 00:42:51,482
These peppers are so plump and good.

625
00:42:51,482 --> 00:42:52,842
Whoa, seriously.

626
00:42:53,581 --> 00:42:54,610
What's going on?

627
00:42:54,610 --> 00:42:56,362
Why did you come out here?

628
00:42:56,362 --> 00:42:57,590
Is someone moving in?

629
00:42:57,590 --> 00:42:58,656
Which floor are they going to?

630
00:42:58,656 --> 00:43:00,408
You know...

631
00:43:00,408 --> 00:43:01,951
As far as I know,

632
00:43:01,951 --> 00:43:04,579
nobody left this morning...

633
00:43:04,579 --> 00:43:07,123
Mom, they destroyed your peppers.

634
00:43:07,123 --> 00:43:09,024
Oh my, what am I going to do?

635
00:43:10,460 --> 00:43:12,003
Seems like we have a new neighbor.

636
00:43:12,003 --> 00:43:13,254
Yeah.

637
00:43:13,254 --> 00:43:16,174
Oh my, look at you! Here is our Summer...

638
00:43:16,174 --> 00:43:17,592
and here is Spring...

639
00:43:17,592 --> 00:43:19,469
and little Autumn is here too!

640
00:43:19,469 --> 00:43:20,870
It's Daddy.

641
00:43:21,721 --> 00:43:23,056
Hey, Lee Jae Min.

642
00:43:23,056 --> 00:43:24,515
Shouldn't you be out on a delivery?

643
00:43:24,515 --> 00:43:26,208
You checking crypto again?

644
00:43:35,234 --> 00:43:36,486
Excuse me,

645
00:43:36,486 --> 00:43:38,071
which unit are you heading to?

646
00:43:38,071 --> 00:43:40,615
Okay, go to unit 206.

647
00:43:40,615 --> 00:43:41,891
206?

648
00:43:54,524 --> 00:43:56,050
Hi, Woo Joo!

649
00:44:04,125 --> 00:44:06,294
- Just drop everything in the living room.
- Yes.

650
00:44:06,294 --> 00:44:07,962
Hold on,

651
00:44:07,962 --> 00:44:09,839
what's happening here?

652
00:44:09,839 --> 00:44:12,366
The baby's aunt.

653
00:44:13,134 --> 00:44:16,178
You said I'm incredibly dependable.

654
00:44:16,178 --> 00:44:17,888
You're super responsible.

655
00:44:17,888 --> 00:44:20,558
And the baby and I have incredible chemistry.

656
00:44:20,558 --> 00:44:22,310
And you and Woo Joo have amazing chemistry.

657
00:44:22,310 --> 00:44:25,062
And you mentioned you'd like

658
00:44:25,062 --> 00:44:26,981
to raise the baby here with me.

659
00:44:26,981 --> 00:44:28,774
To be honest, if you don't mind,

660
00:44:28,774 --> 00:44:31,343
I'd love to raise Woo Joo here
with you anytime.

661
00:44:34,363 --> 00:44:35,698
So you don't actually mean

662
00:44:35,698 --> 00:44:37,766
you're moving in, do you?

663
00:44:38,784 --> 00:44:41,329
Sure, this is Woo Joo's place,

664
00:44:41,329 --> 00:44:42,663
but...

665
00:44:42,663 --> 00:44:44,415
I'm already living here.

666
00:44:44,415 --> 00:44:46,066
And why is that an issue?

667
00:44:46,751 --> 00:44:47,943
We've

668
00:44:55,885 --> 00:44:57,058
already

669
00:44:57,970 --> 00:44:59,204
stripped

670
00:45:00,598 --> 00:45:01,915
down together.

671
00:45:03,100 --> 00:45:05,127
We've already stripped together.

672
00:45:05,770 --> 00:45:07,104
Going forward,

673
00:45:07,104 --> 00:45:08,422
skip the phone calls,

674
00:45:09,607 --> 00:45:11,300
just knock on the door.

675
00:45:13,694 --> 00:45:15,279
I appreciate

676
00:45:15,279 --> 00:45:16,805
your cooperation.

677
00:45:21,952 --> 00:45:24,622
Cooperation for what?

678
00:45:24,622 --> 00:45:25,790
How does any of this make sense?

679
00:45:25,790 --> 00:45:28,793
The two of us living together?

680
00:45:28,793 --> 00:45:30,836
Then,

681
00:45:30,836 --> 00:45:34,548
do you have 5.36 million won?

682
00:45:34,548 --> 00:45:36,217
5.36 million won?

683
00:45:36,217 --> 00:45:38,452
- What are you talking about?
- Damage compensation.

684
00:45:40,846 --> 00:45:42,217
This is the scene of the incident

685
00:45:42,217 --> 00:45:43,766
from the day

686
00:45:43,766 --> 00:45:45,286
you left the baby with me and disappeared.

687
00:45:45,286 --> 00:45:46,977
[Seat replacement, one million]
On that exact day

688
00:45:46,977 --> 00:45:48,793
[Carpet cleaning, one million]
when you left for your interview,

689
00:45:48,793 --> 00:45:49,814
this is the tragic evidence

690
00:45:49,814 --> 00:45:51,882
[Marble repair, one million won]
of all the damage I suffered.

691
00:45:52,547 --> 00:45:55,094
If you're still not convinced,

692
00:45:55,897 --> 00:45:57,154
here's more from that same day.

693
00:45:57,154 --> 00:46:01,450
On that exact day
when you went to your interview,

694
00:46:01,450 --> 00:46:03,327
thanks to the phone

695
00:46:03,327 --> 00:46:04,829
Woo Joo wrecked,

696
00:46:04,829 --> 00:46:06,789
I missed the contractor payment
and the critical window,

697
00:46:06,789 --> 00:46:08,833
which led to a complete catastrophe.

698
00:46:08,833 --> 00:46:10,918
As a result, my move-in

699
00:46:10,918 --> 00:46:12,569
was delayed by a full month.

700
00:46:13,337 --> 00:46:15,423
The bill for all of this

701
00:46:15,423 --> 00:46:18,575
is exactly 5.36 million won.

702
00:46:22,596 --> 00:46:23,876
Wait,

703
00:46:23,876 --> 00:46:25,423
you're not seriously

704
00:46:25,423 --> 00:46:28,688
telling me you plan to stay here, are you?

705
00:46:28,688 --> 00:46:30,229
This is simply temporary shelter

706
00:46:30,229 --> 00:46:31,964
for myself and my babies.

707
00:46:34,859 --> 00:46:36,527
But strictly speaking,

708
00:46:36,527 --> 00:46:38,529
we're not even related,

709
00:46:38,529 --> 00:46:40,114
and beyond that,

710
00:46:40,114 --> 00:46:42,516
you're a man and I'm a woman.

711
00:46:43,826 --> 00:46:45,411
Hang on,

712
00:46:45,411 --> 00:46:47,062
do you actually view me as a man?

713
00:46:48,080 --> 00:46:50,624
Of course not.

714
00:46:50,624 --> 00:46:53,068
You're so not my type.

715
00:46:54,879 --> 00:46:57,256
The feeling is mutual.

716
00:46:57,256 --> 00:46:58,883
You're simply Woo Joo's aunt to me,

717
00:46:58,883 --> 00:47:01,010
that's all you are.

718
00:47:01,010 --> 00:47:02,011
Then it's settled,

719
00:47:02,011 --> 00:47:04,538
we can live together just fine.

720
00:47:05,649 --> 00:47:08,635
No, this still isn't okay.

721
00:47:08,635 --> 00:47:09,994
Wait, hold on.

722
00:47:10,770 --> 00:47:13,153
Why am I seeking approval from you

723
00:47:13,153 --> 00:47:16,066
when someone else actually owns this place?

724
00:47:16,066 --> 00:47:18,040
By your own logic,

725
00:47:18,040 --> 00:47:19,753
the owner here isn't you,

726
00:47:19,753 --> 00:47:21,763
it's Woo Joo.

727
00:47:26,327 --> 00:47:27,912
When I think about it,

728
00:47:27,912 --> 00:47:30,080
at the funeral, Woo Joo was
the true chief mourner.

729
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:31,899
Which means Woo Joo is also the true owner.

730
00:47:32,833 --> 00:47:34,794
So, what's your take?

731
00:47:34,794 --> 00:47:36,921
Can I be your tenant?

732
00:47:36,921 --> 00:47:38,380
Huh?

733
00:47:38,380 --> 00:47:39,489
Yes.

734
00:47:40,841 --> 00:47:42,676
Sure.

735
00:47:42,676 --> 00:47:44,077
See? He said yes.

736
00:47:50,309 --> 00:47:51,668
Ta-da.

737
00:48:39,291 --> 00:48:40,901
At your service, Master.

738
00:48:44,488 --> 00:48:45,948
Woo Joo, what's in your mouth?

739
00:48:45,948 --> 00:48:47,449
Please tell me that's not chocolate.

740
00:48:47,449 --> 00:48:48,993
For breakfast today we have

741
00:48:48,993 --> 00:48:50,578
hormone-free chicken breast,

742
00:48:50,578 --> 00:48:52,329
organic rice, locally grown cabbage,

743
00:48:52,329 --> 00:48:53,539
and Korean carrots.

744
00:48:53,539 --> 00:48:54,928
Need me to continue?

745
00:48:58,633 --> 00:48:59,837
It's excellent for longevity.

746
00:48:59,837 --> 00:49:01,154
This is decaf.

747
00:49:03,013 --> 00:49:04,846
And this is for your Vitamin D synthesis.

748
00:49:58,568 --> 00:50:00,451
Here, here.

749
00:50:34,020 --> 00:50:35,057
Woo Hyun Jin.

750
00:50:35,057 --> 00:50:36,792
Don't fall for this.

751
00:50:41,862 --> 00:50:44,263
[Congratulations on passing
the final selection]

752
00:50:48,737 --> 00:50:50,555
Woo Joo!

753
00:50:51,156 --> 00:50:52,989
I got the BS job!

754
00:50:52,989 --> 00:50:55,035
Oh, congrats.

755
00:50:55,035 --> 00:50:56,245
Woo Joo, clap.

756
00:50:56,245 --> 00:50:57,079
Clap.

757
00:50:57,079 --> 00:50:58,831
Give your auntie a "thumbs up".

758
00:50:58,831 --> 00:51:00,797
That's right.

759
00:51:00,797 --> 00:51:01,875
You know,

760
00:51:01,875 --> 00:51:03,002
rather than hanging around here,

761
00:51:03,002 --> 00:51:04,753
why not go out with your friends?

762
00:51:04,753 --> 00:51:06,296
Step outside, breathe some fresh air,

763
00:51:06,296 --> 00:51:07,739
treat yourself to something tasty.

764
00:51:08,465 --> 00:51:10,175
Pick up some outfits for work.

765
00:51:10,175 --> 00:51:12,953
Don't worry about Woo Joo or the house.

766
00:51:14,263 --> 00:51:15,872
Say bye, Auntie's going out.

767
00:51:21,520 --> 00:51:23,046
Woo Joo, I'll be back.

768
00:51:26,379 --> 00:51:27,401
Does this make any sense?

769
00:51:27,401 --> 00:51:30,654
He's a man, I'm a woman,

770
00:51:30,654 --> 00:51:32,031
how can we live together?

771
00:51:32,031 --> 00:51:33,323
Men and women should keep their distance.

772
00:51:33,323 --> 00:51:35,308
Nobody's asking you to share a bed with him.

773
00:51:35,915 --> 00:51:36,952
Why wouldn't you though?

774
00:51:36,952 --> 00:51:39,246
Just be housemates, nothing more.

775
00:51:39,246 --> 00:51:40,706
Honestly, I see no problem with it.

776
00:51:40,706 --> 00:51:42,875
If anything, it's beneficial.

777
00:51:42,875 --> 00:51:44,168
With childcare and chores,

778
00:51:44,168 --> 00:51:46,086
you can divide it all evenly.

779
00:51:46,086 --> 00:51:47,321
Evenly?

780
00:51:52,426 --> 00:51:53,635
Not a chance.

781
00:51:53,635 --> 00:51:55,054
Absolutely not.

782
00:51:55,054 --> 00:51:56,680
Yesterday he stormed in

783
00:51:56,680 --> 00:51:59,332
and I got caught off guard,

784
00:52:00,100 --> 00:52:02,061
but tonight I will

785
00:52:02,061 --> 00:52:03,312
definitely kick that man out.

786
00:52:03,312 --> 00:52:05,481
All I need to do is survive one month.

787
00:52:05,481 --> 00:52:08,108
If I just stay on that woman's good side,

788
00:52:08,108 --> 00:52:09,735
I can save on rent and storage,

789
00:52:09,735 --> 00:52:12,613
no problem.

790
00:52:12,613 --> 00:52:14,865
What a touching effort.

791
00:52:14,865 --> 00:52:17,868
Signing up to be a servant
just for your furniture.

792
00:52:17,868 --> 00:52:19,620
Classic move from a former lackey,

793
00:52:19,620 --> 00:52:21,580
you really understand what people want.

794
00:52:21,580 --> 00:52:23,248
It's freezing.

795
00:52:23,248 --> 00:52:25,209
Not a servant, it's called strategy.

796
00:52:25,209 --> 00:52:27,336
It's pure paternal devotion to my babies.

797
00:52:28,295 --> 00:52:29,588
After those repair costs,

798
00:52:29,588 --> 00:52:31,590
my account's down to 153,000 won,

799
00:52:31,590 --> 00:52:33,467
and the loan payment is due soon.

800
00:52:33,467 --> 00:52:34,968
But you know how things between men and women

801
00:52:34,968 --> 00:52:36,453
can get complicated.

802
00:52:37,179 --> 00:52:38,347
What if you end up

803
00:52:38,347 --> 00:52:39,723
catching feelings for her?

804
00:52:39,723 --> 00:52:41,642
Catch feelings? Not in a million years.

805
00:52:41,642 --> 00:52:44,353
But that woman seemed
really set on getting rid of you.

806
00:52:44,353 --> 00:52:46,236
What if she doesn't back down?

807
00:52:46,236 --> 00:52:48,190
Not going to happen.

808
00:52:48,190 --> 00:52:50,943
Even fate is working in my favor.

809
00:52:50,943 --> 00:52:52,260
She...

810
00:52:53,612 --> 00:52:55,096
landed a job.

811
00:53:06,291 --> 00:53:07,417
Hyun Jin.

812
00:53:07,417 --> 00:53:08,710
You're not buying anything?

813
00:53:08,710 --> 00:53:10,546
Let me buy you something to celebrate your job.

814
00:53:10,546 --> 00:53:12,756
No, I already have enough clothes.

815
00:53:12,756 --> 00:53:15,092
What are you reading?

816
00:53:15,092 --> 00:53:17,953
I've got to find childcare for Woo Joo,

817
00:53:19,000 --> 00:53:20,997
but nannies cost over 2 million won.

818
00:53:21,646 --> 00:53:23,642
And daycares are all backed up...

819
00:53:23,642 --> 00:53:24,935
Gosh.

820
00:53:24,935 --> 00:53:27,963
Adapting to our company at first
is going to be really demanding.

821
00:53:28,689 --> 00:53:30,065
Exactly.

822
00:53:31,030 --> 00:53:32,109
Woo Joo and I are both

823
00:53:32,109 --> 00:53:34,511
going to need time to settle in.

824
00:53:38,574 --> 00:53:40,242
You think that woman

825
00:53:40,242 --> 00:53:42,536
will actually follow your grand plan?

826
00:53:42,536 --> 00:53:43,704
Just wait and see.

827
00:53:43,704 --> 00:53:47,082
She'll reach out to me
in less than ten minutes.

828
00:53:47,082 --> 00:53:48,250
Ten minutes.

829
00:53:48,250 --> 00:53:51,634
Tick tock tick tock...

830
00:53:51,634 --> 00:53:52,713
Just consider that guy

831
00:53:52,713 --> 00:53:54,256
a short-term assistant.

832
00:53:54,256 --> 00:53:56,216
Hire him, use him, endure him.

833
00:53:56,216 --> 00:53:58,218
You hold all the power anyway.

834
00:53:58,218 --> 00:53:59,928
Still, something about it feels wrong.

835
00:53:59,928 --> 00:54:01,638
Hyun Jin.

836
00:54:01,638 --> 00:54:05,601
Suppress that old-fashioned mindset of yours.

837
00:54:05,601 --> 00:54:07,419
Just think about what benefits you now.

838
00:54:11,190 --> 00:54:12,382
All right.

839
00:54:15,152 --> 00:54:16,862
I got a message.

840
00:54:16,862 --> 00:54:20,032
There's something pressing we should sort out,

841
00:54:20,032 --> 00:54:21,909
don't you think?

842
00:54:21,909 --> 00:54:24,269
Let's talk in the living room at seven tonight.

843
00:54:28,332 --> 00:54:29,458
One month.

844
00:54:29,458 --> 00:54:32,628
Exactly one month, no longer.

845
00:54:32,628 --> 00:54:33,795
Let's do nine to six.

846
00:54:33,795 --> 00:54:35,005
During my hours at BS,

847
00:54:35,005 --> 00:54:37,324
I need you to look after Woo Joo completely.

848
00:54:38,431 --> 00:54:39,468
Agreed.

849
00:54:39,468 --> 00:54:42,262
And keep the apartment tidy while you're at it.

850
00:54:42,262 --> 00:54:44,765
Just maintain things like you have been.

851
00:54:44,765 --> 00:54:45,766
Auntie.

852
00:54:45,766 --> 00:54:47,083
Yeah.

853
00:54:49,228 --> 00:54:50,646
Okay.

854
00:54:50,646 --> 00:54:52,356
But it's fifty-fifty.

855
00:54:52,356 --> 00:54:55,425
In good conscience, as co-residents.

856
00:54:56,181 --> 00:54:57,319
Agreed.

857
00:54:57,319 --> 00:54:58,862
Water, gas, electric,

858
00:54:58,862 --> 00:55:00,113
wifi included,

859
00:55:00,113 --> 00:55:01,848
all split in half.

860
00:55:06,870 --> 00:55:08,163
Done.

861
00:55:08,163 --> 00:55:10,624
And since Woo Joo technically owns this place,

862
00:55:10,624 --> 00:55:12,751
his diapers and formula

863
00:55:12,751 --> 00:55:14,194
are also split evenly.

864
00:55:15,545 --> 00:55:16,946
Fine, agreed.

865
00:55:18,048 --> 00:55:19,597
Agreed.

866
00:55:19,597 --> 00:55:20,849
[Roommate Agreement]

867
00:56:22,759 --> 00:56:23,761
Pimang?

868
00:56:23,761 --> 00:56:24,927
Looks like something's on it.

869
00:56:24,927 --> 00:56:26,532
No, forget it. Don't buy it.

870
00:56:27,206 --> 00:56:28,261
Pimang guy?

871
00:56:28,261 --> 00:56:30,777
So you really are Woo Jin's brother?

872
00:56:30,777 --> 00:56:32,289
- One random day,
- One random day,

873
00:56:32,289 --> 00:56:34,052
- another "universe"
- another "universe"

874
00:56:34,052 --> 00:56:35,469
- suddenly dropped into it.
- suddenly dropped into it.

875
00:56:35,469 --> 00:56:36,469
Mommy.

876
00:56:36,469 --> 00:56:39,672
What am I supposed to do with the baby?

877
00:56:39,672 --> 00:56:42,386
We need to decide which of you will raise him.

878
00:56:42,386 --> 00:56:44,093
What? You smiling?

879
00:56:44,093 --> 00:56:45,386
This is not the time to smile.

880
00:56:45,386 --> 00:56:46,706
Read the room.

881
00:56:48,264 --> 00:56:50,487
Why did you...

882
00:56:50,487 --> 00:56:51,767
Why did you just leave the baby with me?

883
00:56:51,767 --> 00:56:52,810
I'll raise him.

884
00:56:52,810 --> 00:56:54,927
I'll take care of Woo Joo.

885
00:56:54,927 --> 00:56:56,535
Will you actually be fine?

886
00:56:57,386 --> 00:56:58,678
Woo Joo and I will get by

887
00:56:58,678 --> 00:57:00,286
perfectly fine without him.

888
00:57:00,969 --> 00:57:02,528
Look at this place...

889
00:57:02,528 --> 00:57:04,446
Seriously, how are you planning
to do this by yourself?

890
00:57:04,446 --> 00:57:05,511
I have to get in

891
00:57:05,511 --> 00:57:08,350
so I can raise Woo Joo right.

892
00:57:11,120 --> 00:57:13,302
Your place is flooded right now.

893
00:57:13,302 --> 00:57:15,761
So when will I be able to move in?

894
00:57:15,761 --> 00:57:18,127
At least another month.

895
00:57:18,127 --> 00:57:20,136
Hold on, what's happening here?

896
00:57:20,136 --> 00:57:22,803
So you don't actually mean
you're moving in, do you?

897
00:57:22,803 --> 00:57:25,302
Just consider that guy a short-term assistant.

898
00:57:25,302 --> 00:57:27,719
With childcare and chores,
you can divide it all evenly.

899
00:57:27,719 --> 00:57:28,469
One month.

900
00:57:28,469 --> 00:57:30,678
I need you to look after Woo Joo completely.

901
00:57:30,678 --> 00:57:32,017
Done.

902
00:57:32,017 --> 00:57:33,052
Agreed.

903
00:57:33,052 --> 00:57:35,702
I appreciate your cooperation.

904
00:57:38,530 --> 00:57:39,929
Make sure you knock

905
00:57:40,572 --> 00:57:41,905
when you need me.

906
00:57:41,905 --> 00:57:43,574
Hold on, you don't have work?

907
00:57:43,574 --> 00:57:45,905
How can you look after Woo Joo
while I'm at work?

908
00:57:45,905 --> 00:57:48,281
You're so useless.

909
00:57:48,281 --> 00:57:51,156
Just until I find my footing at the company.

910
00:57:51,156 --> 00:57:54,072
Hello, I'm Park Yoon Seong,
manager of Planning Team 3.

911
00:57:54,072 --> 00:57:57,947
I really wanted Yoon Seong
to only see me at my best.

912
00:57:57,947 --> 00:57:59,215
- Let me have it.
- No way.

913
00:57:59,215 --> 00:58:01,384
What if you end up falling for that woman?

914
00:58:01,384 --> 00:58:02,905
No, Woo Joo.

915
00:58:02,905 --> 00:58:04,245
No!

916
00:58:04,947 --> 00:58:07,039
Oh crap.
